  "prompt": "Where can I study at Stanford?",
  "response": "Stanford University offers a wide range of study options across its seven schools, which include undergraduate, graduate, and professional programs. Here are the main schools and areas of study:\n\n1. **School of Humanities and Sciences**:\n   - Offers undergraduate and graduate programs in disciplines such as English, history, psychology, biology, chemistry, physics, mathematics, and many more.\n\n2. **School of Engineering**:\n   - Programs in areas like computer science, electrical engineering, mechanical engineering, bioengineering, and more. They offer undergraduate, graduate, and doctoral programs.\n\n3. **Graduate School of Business**:\n   - Offers the MBA program, MSx Program (for experienced professionals), and a PhD program in various business disciplines.\n\n4. **School of Law**:\n   - Offers the Juris Doctor (JD) program, Master of Laws (LLM) program, and the Doctor of the Science of Law (JSD) program.\n\n5. **School of Medicine**:\n   - Offers MD, PhD programs, and various master's programs in medical sciences and health research.\n\n6. **School of Earth, Energy & Environmental Sciences**:\n   - Programs in fields such as earth systems, energy resources engineering, geological and environmental sciences. Offering undergraduate and graduate degrees.\n\n7. **Graduate School of Education**:\n   - Offers master\u2019s, doctoral, and joint degree programs in education and related fields.\n\n**Admission Requirements**:\n- **Undergraduate**: High school diploma or equivalent, standardized test scores (SAT/ACT), essays, letters of recommendation, extracurricular activities, and academic achievements.\n- **Graduate**: Bachelor\u2019s degree, GRE/GMAT scores (depending on the program), letters of recommendation, statement of purpose, and relevant work or research experience.\n\n**Application Process**:\n- Applications are typically submitted online through the Stanford University admissions portal.\n- Specific program requirements and deadlines can be found on the respective school\u2019s website.\n\n**Financial Aid**:\n- Stanford offers need-based financial aid for undergraduate students and various scholarships, fellowships, and assistantships for graduate students.\n- The university is committed to meeting 100% of demonstrated financial need for undergraduates.\n\n**Additional Information**:\n- Stanford also offers interdisciplinary programs, research opportunities, and study abroad programs.\n- Prospective students can visit the official Stanford University website for detailed information on programs, admissions, and campus life.\n\nFor specific inquiries, it\u2019s best to contact the admissions office of the particular school or program you\u2019re interested in.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
